    {
        "content": "<p>Is there any usage for <code>Atomic{I,U}8</code> and <code>Atomic{I,U}16</code> in debugfs? If no, can we remove them? We are not supposed to rust atomics.</p>",
        "id": 546354382,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1761099233
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"554954\">@Matthew Maurer</span> ^</p>",
        "id": 546354518,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1761099356
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Using <code>AtomicUsize</code> becasue <code>Atomic&lt;T&gt;</code> was not available is one thing, but adding the support of <code>AtomicI8</code>, <code>AtomicU8</code>, <code>AtomicU16</code> and <code>AtomicI16</code> is another.</p>",
        "id": 546354948,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1761099780
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Which atomics are we meant to be using? I thought adding support for kernel-style atomics wasn't done yet</p>",
        "id": 546358734,
        "sender_full_name": "Matthew Maurer",
        "timestamp": 1761103546
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>kernel atomics are added already.</p>",
        "id": 546358794,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1761103593
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but all not the sizes</p>",
        "id": 546358806,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1761103602
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I actually figured out what changes are needed for debugfs, please see <a href=\"https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/boqun/linux.git/log/?h=debugfs-atomic\">here</a></p>",
        "id": 546358865,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1761103656
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ok, I was going to say, if they're there I can switch the blanket impls over</p>",
        "id": 546358907,
        "sender_full_name": "Matthew Maurer",
        "timestamp": 1761103704
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But if you've already done it, great</p>",
        "id": 546358944,
        "sender_full_name": "Matthew Maurer",
        "timestamp": 1761103756
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(I can take a look at the actual code tomorrow if you'd like)</p>",
        "id": 546358971,
        "sender_full_name": "Matthew Maurer",
        "timestamp": 1761103780
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks! I thought it can be done in that way, but turned out it needs some more atomic changes, so I just took a deep look.</p>",
